Equilibrium shapes, resulting from minimizing the bending energy F BE, have been extensively studied, see ref. 6 for a review. For H 0 = 0 and wide ranges

of the reduced volume, which is the ratio of the volume and the volume of an

equivalent sphere with the same area, they are dominated by prolate and oblate

